OL,6,FIn a troubling new development, the UK
OL,7,FMedicines and Healthcare Regulatory
OL,8,FAgency (MHRA) has now admitted that it
OL,9,Fmisled the public for more than a
OL,10,Fdecade.
OL,12,FThe medicines regulator falsely
OL,13,Fclaimed that the drug was banned for
OL,14,Fuse in pre-menopausal women in 1973, a
OL,15,Fstatement which our reporting has
OL,16,Fexposed was inaccurate, leading to an
OL,17,Fapology from the MHRA for "this error
OL,18,Fand for any distress caused to
OL,19,Fpatients and the public".
