OL,6,FFor one family from Worcester, the
OL,7,Flegacy of DES has been devastating
OL,8,Fwith the harmful effects of the drug
OL,9,Fpassed down the generations and they
OL,10,Fbelieve they were poisoned in the womb.
OL,12,FSisters Michelle Taylor, 63, and
OL,13,FChristine Holt, 71, believe that the
OL,14,Fdrug is to blame for a lifetime of
OL,15,Fhealth problems after their mother
OL,16,FSylvia Bennett was prescribed DES
OL,17,Ffollowing a string of miscarriages in
OL,18,Fthe 1960s.
